Quote:  Bush fighting is a comprehensive term for warfare conducted in forests, in broken ground and on the hill-side. Whereever cover can be got, in attack and defence, under the canopy of heaven, there bush fighting can be practised, and it is highly useful to practise it as a part of army manoeuvres.
